<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g867884g65f41.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">1801 Bayberry Court </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">P.O. Box 18100 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">Richmond, VA 23226-8100 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">March 27, 2020 </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To Our Shareholders: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On behalf of the Board of Directors, we invite you to attend
the annual meeting of shareholders of The Brink&#146;s Company on Friday, May&nbsp;8, 2020 at 10:00 a.m. local time at the Hilton Dallas/Southlake Town Square, 1400&nbsp;Plaza Place, Southlake, Texas 76092. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">2019 capped off our three year strategic plan period in which we exceeded the financial targets we set out for the Company in March 2017 through the execution of
breakthrough initiatives to increase efficiency and profitability and disciplined execution of accretive acquisitions. Our Compensation Committee and Board continue to adhere to a philosophy that aligns pay and performance through awards of annual
and long-term incentives that balance management performance and shareholder returns. Despite the uncertainty we and other companies are experiencing in early 2020, we believe we are well-positioned for success over our next three year plan period.
We remain dedicated to growing our Company and continuing to deliver value to our shareholders, while maintaining our high standards of corporate governance and our unwavering commitment to safety and security for our customers and employees. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Your vote at the annual shareholder meeting is important. Whether or not you plan to attend the meeting, we urge you to vote as soon as possible. There are two ways to
vote. You can complete, sign, date and return the enclosed proxy in the envelope provided or you can vote on the internet. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We look forward to seeing you at the
annual meeting and thank you for your continued support. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Sincerely, </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

 </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:1.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:15pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:-15pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>NOTICE OF ANNUAL MEETING OF SHAREHOLDERS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:18pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>TO BE HELD MAY&nbsp;8, 2020 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:1.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The annual meeting of shareholders of THE BRINK&#146;S
COMPANY will be held on May&nbsp;8, 2020 at 10:00 a.m. local time at the Hilton Dallas/Southlake Town Square, 1400 Plaza Place, Southlake, Texas 76092 for the following purposes: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

expiring in 2021. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

year ending December&nbsp;31, 2020. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The close of business on March&nbsp;2, 2020 has been fixed as the record date for determining the shareholders entitled to notice of and to vote
at the annual meeting. This proxy statement and the accompanying form of proxy and annual report to shareholders are being mailed to shareholders of record as of the close of business on March&nbsp;2, 2020, commencing on or about April&nbsp;6, 2020.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Please note that brokers may not vote your shares on the election of directors or the advisory vote on named executive officer compensation in the absence of your
specific instructions as to how to vote. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We intend to hold our annual meeting in person. However, we are actively monitoring the coronavirus <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(COVID-19)</FONT> and we are sensitive to the public health and travel concerns our shareholders may have and the protocols that federal, state, and local governments may impose. In the event it is not possible or
advisable to hold our annual meeting in person, we will announce alternative arrangements for the meeting as promptly as practicable, which may include holding the meeting solely by means of remote communication. Please monitor our annual meeting
website at http://investors.brinks.com/2020annualmeetingmaterials for updated information. If you are planning to attend our meeting, please check the website one week prior to the meeting date. As always, we encourage you to vote your shares prior
to the annual meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>YOUR VOTE IS IMPORTANT. WHETHER OR NOT YOU PLAN TO ATTEND THE MEETING, PLEASE MARK, SIGN, DATE AND MAIL THE ENCLOSED PROXY CARD OR VOTE ON
THE INTERNET. A RETURN ENVELOPE IS ENCLOSED FOR YOUR CONVENIENCE. </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Lindsay K. Blackwood </P>

<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_1"></A>PROXY SUMMARY </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To help you review The Brink&#146;s Company&#146;s (&#147;Brink&#146;s&#148; or the &#147;Company&#148;) 2020 proxy
statement, we have summarized several key topics below. The following description is only a summary.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For more complete information about these topics, please review the complete proxy statement and the Company&#146;s 2019
Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K.</FONT> </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2019 Highlights </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Brink&#146;s is the global leader in total cash management, route-based logistics and payment solutions, including <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">cash-in-transit,</FONT></FONT> ATM services, cash management services, including vault outsourcing, money processing and intelligent safe services, and international transportation of
valuables to financial institutions, retailers, government agencies (including central banks), mints, jewelers and other commercial operations around the world. We serve customers in more than 100 countries and have approximately
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
64,600 employees worldwide. A significant portion of our business is conducted internationally, with approximately 67% of our revenues earned outside the United States. Brink&#146;s reported
strong earnings growth in 2019. Following are key financial performance metrics that are monitored by management and the Board, reported to shareholders, and used in determining 2019 compensation for the named executive officers.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g867884g38g27.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:8.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:16%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">*</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">These <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> financial measures are not presented in accordance with U.S.
generally accepted accounting principles (&#147;GAAP&#148;). See page 34 of the Company&#146;s Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2019 for a reconciliation of <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> operating profit and revenue to the most directly comparable GAAP financial measures. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Executive
Compensation Program </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our executive compensation program is structured to link compensation to Company and individual performance over the
short- and long-term and to align the interests of executives and shareholders. We do this by using shares of the Company&#146;s common stock (&#147;Brink&#146;s Common Stock&#148;) and
stock-</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
based awards in our incentive compensation programs and by maintaining robust executive stock ownership guidelines. Elements of compensation for Brink&#146;s executives include base salary,
annual incentives and long-term incentives (&#147;LTI&#148;). </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

</SUB>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2020 Proxy Statement&nbsp;&nbsp;</I></TD>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Performance-Based and Variable Compensation in 2019 </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#0033a0"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Annual</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Incentives</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Annual Incentive
Award</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Provides a cash award based on achievement of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-established</FONT> <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-year</FONT> <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> operating profit and revenue goals as well as free cash flow results and individual performance.</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B></B></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#0033a0"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Long
Term</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.67em; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Incentives </B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Internal Metric Performance Share Units (&#147;Internal
Metric PSUs&#148;)</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Paid out in shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at the end of a three-year performance period, based on achievement of a <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-established</FONT> three-year total <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> EBITDA performance goal, and subject to a three-year vesting requirement. Represents 50% of the total LTI award for the Chief
Executive Officer and 25% of the total LTI award for the other named executive officers.</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#0033a0"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Relative Total Shareholder Return (&#147;TSR&#148;) Performance Share Units (&#147;Relative TSR PSUs&#148;)</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Paid out in shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at the end of a three-year performance period, based on the Company&#146;s TSR relative to that of companies in the
S&amp;P MidCap 400 with foreign revenues equal to or exceeding 50% of total revenues. Represents 25% of the total LTI award for each of the named executive officers.</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#0033a0"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Stock Options</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Each option represents the
opportunity to purchase one share of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at the end of a three&#150;year vesting period at the price per share on the grant date. Represents 25% of the total LTI award for each of the named executive officers.</I></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#0033a0"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Restricted Stock Units (&#147;RSUs&#148;)</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Paid out in shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock and vesting in three equal annual installments. Represents 25% of the total LTI award for the named executive officers
other than the Chief Executive Officer.</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2019, performance-based compensation (which includes annual incentives, Internal Metric PSUs, Relative TSR PSUs, and
Stock Options) represented approximately 88% of total target compensation for the Chief Executive Officer and approximately 59% of
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
total target compensation (on average) for the Company&#146;s other named executive officers who were serving as of December&nbsp;31, 2019, as illustrated below. See pages 37-41 for additional
information about the long-term incentive awards. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">

 </P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>PROXY SUMMARY </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2019 Compensation Decisions </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In February 2019, the Compensation and Benefits Committee (the &#147;Compensation Committee&#148;) approved LTI awards of
Internal Metric PSUs, Relative TSR PSUs, Stock Options and RSUs to the Company&#146;s named executive officers. Payouts of 2019 annual incentives to named executive officers were approved by the Compensation Committee in February 2020 ranging from
approximately 77% to 107% of target (depending on the named executive officer), reflecting corporate performance, performance in the countries within each executive&#146;s area of responsibility (where applicable), and individual performance. The
corporate performance factor for 2019 payouts was determined by performance that was below the target levels of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> operating profit and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> revenue goals,
as well as performance slightly below the free
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
cash flow performance goal. In February 2020, the Compensation Committee also approved payouts for LTI awards granted in 2017, which consisted of Internal Metric PSUs, Relative TSR PSUs and RSUs.
Relative TSR PSUs were paid out in shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at 150% of target, reflecting relative TSR above the 75th percentile of peer companies and stock price appreciation of approximately 226% over the three-year period. Internal
Metric PSUs were paid out in shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at 200% of target, reflecting performance that was above the target level for the three-year <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> operating profit goal beginning
January&nbsp;1, 2017 and ending December&nbsp;31, 2019. These compensation decisions are more fully described in the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, beginning on page 27.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Corporate Governance </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Brink&#146;s is committed to good corporate governance and employs a number of practices that the Company&#146;s Board of
Directors (the &#147;Board&#148;) has
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
determined are in the best interest of the Company and our shareholders. Following are examples of those practices.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>What We Do and Don&#146;t Do:
</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9.5pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="27%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="68%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="7" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#0033a0"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>We strive to employ good</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>governance practices</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT>
Chairman</B>&#151;The Board annually appoints a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT> Chairman of the Board and is structured to have a lead director if the Board determines to combine the roles of Chairman of the Board and Chief
Executive Officer. This framework ensures the Board operates independently of management and that directors and shareholders have an independent leadership contact.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Majority Vote Standard</B>&#151;A director must tender his
or her resignation if his or her election receives less than a majority vote in an uncontested election.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Executive Sessions</B>&#151;The independent members of the
Board hold an executive session at each regular Board meeting.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Annual Director Elections</B>&#151;Each director stands
for election by the Company&#146;s shareholders each year.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Say on Pay</B>&#151;We provide shareholders with an annual
advisory vote on named executive officer compensation.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Proxy Access</B>&#151;A shareholder, or group of up to 20
shareholders, who have continuously owned at least 3% of our outstanding Common Stock for three years or more may nominate and include in our proxy statement up to the greater of two director nominees or 20% of our Board.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Special
Meetings</B>&#151;Shareholders holding at least 20% of our outstanding common stock may call a special meeting.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#0033a0"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Our compensation</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>program is designed to</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>align with shareholder</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>interests</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><B>Pay for Performance</B>&#151;Our executive compensation program links compensation to Company and individual performance over both the short- and long-term.</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><B>Stock Ownership Guidelines</B>&#151;We maintain robust stock ownership guidelines for the Chief Executive Officer and other executive officers.</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Double Trigger
Accelerated Vesting</B>&#151;Equity awards are subject to a &#147;double trigger&#148; for accelerated vesting in the event of a change in control followed by termination of employment.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #ffffff" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="7" BGCOLOR="#0033a0"> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>We
strive to adhere to</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>good executive</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.63em; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>compensation practices</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><B>Recoupment Policy</B>&#151;We maintain a recoupment policy for performance-based cash and equity-based incentive payments in the event of a financial restatement.</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Double Trigger Change in Control Agreements</B>&#151;We
maintain change in control agreements that provide executives with benefits of up to two times the sum of salary and average annual incentive in the event of a change in control followed by termination of employment.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Independent Compensation Consultant</B>&#151;The
Compensation Committee retains an independent compensation consulting firm that provides no other services to the Company.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><I>&times;</I></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>No Tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Gross-ups</FONT>
and No Excessive Perquisites</B>&#151;There are no tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups</FONT> and we provide limited perquisites to executive officers.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><I>&times;</I></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>No Hedging</B>&#151;Directors and executive officers are
prohibited from engaging in hedging transactions with respect to Company securities.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><I>&times;</I></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>No Pledging</B>&#151;Effective January&nbsp;1, 2020,
directors and executive officers are prohibited from pledging Company securities.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"><FONT STYLE="font-size:9.5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><I>&times;</I></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9.5pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>No Repricing of Underwater Stock Options</B>&#151;The
Brink&#146;s Company 2017 Equity Incentive Plan prohibits <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-pricing</FONT> of underwater stock options without shareholder approval.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#e5eaf5"></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="padding-bottom:3pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>Age</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="padding-bottom:3pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>Director</B></FONT></P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="padding-bottom:3pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>Committee Memberships</B></FONT></TD></TR>

<TD HEIGHT="4"></TD>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Shareholder Engagement </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">At last year&#146;s annual meeting of shareholders, over 99% of votes cast approved the &#147;say on pay&#148; proposal
regarding the compensation awarded to named executive officers. The Compensation Committee and the Board take into account the results of the &#147;say on pay&#148; vote as they consider the design of the executive compensation program and policies.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">There were no changes made to the Company&#146;s executive compensation program in direct response to the 2019 &#147;say
on pay&#148; voting results. Members of management and the Board continue to engage in outreach to the Company&#146;s shareholders to discuss governance and compensation policies and practices and emerging
issues.</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Forward Looking Statements </B></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This Proxy Statement contains forward-looking statements within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_2"></A>QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS ABOUT THE </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">ANNUAL MEETING </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The mailing address of the principal
executive office of the Company is 1801 Bayberry Court, P.O. Box 18100, Richmond, VA 23226-8100. Following are questions and answers regarding the annual meeting: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Why am I receiving this proxy statement? </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">You are receiving this proxy statement in connection with the solicitation of proxies by the Board to be voted at the 2020
annual meeting of shareholders (and at any adjournment or postponement of the 2020 annual meeting), for the purposes set forth in the accompanying notice. The annual meeting will be held on May&nbsp;8, 2020, at 10:00 a.m., local time, at the Hilton
Dallas/Southlake Town Square, 1400 Plaza
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
Place, Southlake, Texas 76092. In the event it is not possible or advisable to hold our annual meeting in person, we will announce alternative arrangements for the meeting as promptly as
practicable, which may include holding the meeting solely by means of remote communication. Please monitor our annual meeting website at http://investors.brinks.com/2020annualmeetingmaterials for updated information.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>What is a proxy? </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">A proxy is your legal designation of another person to vote the stock you own. If you designate someone as your proxy in a
written document, that document is also called a proxy (or proxy card). Ronald J. Domanico and Lindsay K. Blackwood have been
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
designated as proxies for the annual meeting. A proxy, if duly executed and not revoked, will be voted and, if it contains any specific instructions, will be voted in accordance with those
instructions. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Who is entitled to vote at the annual meeting?
</B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">You are entitled to notice of the annual meeting and may vote your shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock if you owned them
as of the close of business March&nbsp;2, 2020, which is the date that the Board has designated as the record date for the 2020 annual
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
meeting of shareholders. On March&nbsp;2, 2020, the Company had outstanding 50,435,866 shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock. Each share of Brink&#146;s Common Stock is entitled to one vote.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>How many votes must be present to hold the annual meeting? </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">A majority of the outstanding shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock as of the record date must be present in person or
represented by proxy at the annual meeting. This is referred to as a quorum. Abstentions, withheld votes and shares held in street name (&#147;Brokers&#146; Shares&#148;) voted by brokers are included in determining the number of votes present.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Brokers&#146; Shares that are not voted on any matter will not be included in determining whether a quorum is present. In
the event that a quorum is not present at the annual meeting, we expect that the annual meeting will be adjourned or postponed to solicit additional proxies.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>What is a broker
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-vote?</FONT> </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under the rules of the New York Stock Exchange, a broker may vote Brokers&#146; Shares in its discretion on &#147;routine
matters,&#148; but a broker may not vote on proposals that are not considered &#147;routine.&#148; When a
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
proposal is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-routine</FONT> matter and the broker has not received voting instructions with respect to that proposal, the broker cannot vote on that
proposal. This is commonly called a &#147;broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-vote.&#148;</FONT> </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>How many votes are needed to approve each
proposal? </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table summarizes the vote required to approve each proposal and the effects of abstentions, broker <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes,</FONT> and signed, but unmarked proxy cards, on the tabulation of votes for
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
each proposal. For any other business that may properly come before the annual meeting, proxies will be voted in accordance with the judgment of the person voting the proxies.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="8%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="34%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="17%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="padding-bottom:1pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0.50em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>Proposal</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; text-indent:0.50em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>Number</B></FONT></P></TD>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company&#146;s bylaws provide that the Chairman of the annual meeting will determine the order of business and the
voting and other procedures to be observed at the annual meeting. The Chairman is authorized to declare whether any business is properly brought before the annual meeting, and business not properly brought before the annual meeting will not be
transacted. We are not aware of
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
any matters that are to come before the annual meeting other than those described in this proxy statement. If other matters do properly come before the annual meeting, however, it is the
intention of the persons named in the enclosed proxy card to exercise the discretionary authority conferred by the proxy to vote such proxy in accordance with their best judgment.

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS ABOUT THE ANNUAL MEETING </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Can I revoke my proxy? </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The enclosed proxy is revocable at any time prior to its being voted by filing an instrument of revocation or a duly
executed proxy bearing a later time. A proxy may also be revoked by attendance at the annual meeting and voting in person. See &#147;Questions and
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
Answers About the Annual Meeting&#151;How do I attend the annual meeting? What should I bring?&#148; Attendance at the annual meeting will not by itself constitute a revocation.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Who pays for the solicitation of votes? </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The cost of this solicitation of proxies will be borne by the Company. In addition to soliciting proxies by mail,
directors, officers and employees of the Company, without receiving additional compensation therefor, may solicit proxies by telephone, facsimile, electronic mail, in person or by other means. Arrangements also will be made with brokerage firms and
other custodians, nominees and fiduciaries to forward proxy solicitation material to the beneficial owners of Brink&#146;s Common Stock and the Company will
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
reimburse such brokerage firms, custodians, nominees and fiduciaries for reasonable <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">out-of-pocket</FONT></FONT> expenses in
connection with their solicitation efforts. The Company has retained Innisfree M&amp;A Incorporated to perform proxy advisory and solicitation services. The fee of Innisfree M&amp;A Incorporated in connection with the 2020 annual meeting is
estimated to be approximately $15,000, plus reimbursement of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">out-of-pocket</FONT></FONT> expenses.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>How do I attend the annual meeting? What should I
bring? </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Shareholders who wish to attend the annual meeting and vote in person and who need directions to the annual meeting may
contact the Corporate Secretary at (804) <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">289-9600.</FONT> Shareholders of record who wish to vote in person at the annual meeting will be able to request a ballot at the annual meeting. Shareholders who hold their
shares through a broker in &#147;street name&#148; and who wish to vote in person at the annual meeting will not be able to vote their shares at the annual meeting without a legal proxy from the street name holder of record. Those shareholders
should contact their brokers for further information. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We intend to hold our annual meeting in person. However, we are actively monitoring the coronavirus
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(COVID-19)</FONT> and we are sensitive to the public health and travel concerns our shareholders may have and the protocols that federal, state, and local
governments may impose. In the event it is not possible or advisable to hold our annual meeting in person, we will announce alternative arrangements for the meeting as promptly as practicable, which may include holding the meeting solely by means of
remote communication. Please monitor our annual meeting website at http://investors.brinks.com/2020annualmeetingmaterials for updated information. If you are planning to attend our meeting, please check the website one week prior to the meeting
date. As always, we encourage you to vote your shares prior to the annual meeting. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Who will count the votes? </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Shareholder votes at the annual meeting will be tabulated by the
Company&#146;s transfer agent, American Stock Transfer&nbsp;&amp; Trust Company. </P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_3"></A>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_4"></A>Board of Directors </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Role of the Board of Directors </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board is responsible for advancing the interests of the shareholders by providing advice and oversight of the strategic and operational direction of the Company;
overseeing the governance of the Company and the Company&#146;s executive management, including the Chief Executive Officer; and reviewing the Company&#146;s business initiatives, capital projects and budget matters. To do this effectively, the
Company has established clear and specific Governance Guidelines for the Board (referred to as our Governance Policies) that, along with Board committee charters and our Code of Ethics, provide the framework for the governance of the Company. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Board Leadership Structure </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board
does not have a policy on whether the roles of the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman should be separate. The Board regularly evaluates relevant factors to determine the best leadership structure for the Company&#146;s operating and governance
environment at the time. In accordance with good governance practices, the Board&#146;s policy is to appoint a lead director from among the independent members of the Board in the event that the roles of Chairman and Chief Executive Officer are
combined. In response to significant changes in the Company&#146;s leadership, in 2016, the Board appointed Michael J. Herling as the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-executive</FONT> Chairman of the Board. The Board believes the separation of
the offices of Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer was appropriate at that time as it allowed, and continues to allow, Mr.&nbsp;Pertz to focus primarily on Brink&#146;s business strategy and operations and Mr.&nbsp;Herling to provide
the independent leadership of the Board. As the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-executive</FONT> chairman of the Board, Mr.&nbsp;Herling has the following responsibilities: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">presides over meetings of the Board and shareholders; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">calls meetings and executive sessions of the Board; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">develops the meeting agendas and ensures critical issues are addressed; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">facilitates communication between and among directors and management and
</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="53" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left" COLOR="#000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
ensures the quality, quantity and timing of information from management; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">has a lead role in the evaluation of the Chief Executive Officer; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">serves as the representative of the Board with management and the public and interacts with shareholders on behalf of the Board at the Board&#146;s discretion; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">facilitates communication between the Board and investors, at the Board&#146;s discretion; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">promotes effective communications on developments occurring between Board meetings; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">performs such other duties assigned from time to time by the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If the Chairman and CEO roles were to be combined in
the future, a lead director would be appointed. We expect that a lead director would have the following responsibilities: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">preside over meetings of the independent directors; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">work with the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer to develop meeting agendas and ensure critical issues are addressed; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">act as a principal liaison between independent directors and the Chief Executive Officer and brief the Chief Executive Officer on issues of concern that arise during executive sessions of independent directors;
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">have a lead role in the evaluation of the Chief Executive Officer (if the Chairman also serves as the Chief Executive Officer); </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">take the lead in assuring that the Board carries out its responsibilities in circumstances where the Chief Executive Officer is incapacitated or unable to act; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">serve as the primary <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-management</FONT> contact with shareholders, as needed; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">perform such other duties assigned from time to time by the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
