<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Meetings of the Board and Director Attendance </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board met six times in 2019. During 2019, all incumbent directors attended at least 75% of the total number of meetings of the Board and of the committees of the
Board on which they served. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Executive Sessions of the Board </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-management</FONT> members of the Board meet regularly without management present. The Chairman presides over each meeting of the
independent Board members. </P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Director Attendance at Annual Meeting </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company has no formal policy with regard to Board members&#146; attendance at annual meetings. All of the directors then in office, with the exception of
Mr.&nbsp;Clough, attended the 2019 annual meeting of shareholders. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_5"></A>Board Independence
</B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For a director to be deemed &#147;independent,&#148; the Board must affirmatively determine, in accordance with the
listing standards of the New York Stock Exchange, that the director has no material relationship with the Company, either directly or as a partner, shareholder or officer of an organization that has a relationship with the Company. In making this
determination, the Board has adopted the following categorical standards as part of its Governance Policies: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="27">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="27" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">A director who is, or has been within the last three years, an employee of the Company, or whose immediate family member
is, or has been within the last three years, an executive officer of the Company, is not independent. Employment as an interim Chairman, Chief Executive Officer or other executive officer will not disqualify a director from being considered
independent following such employment. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="27">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="27" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">A director who has received or who has an immediate family member serving as an executive officer who has received,
during any twelve-month period within the last three years, more than $120,000 in direct compensation from the Company (excluding director and committee fees and pensions or other forms of deferred compensation for prior service, provided such
compensation is not contingent in any way on continued service), is not independent. Compensation received by a director for former service as an interim Chairman, Chief Executive Officer or other executive officer will not count toward the $120,000
limitation. </P></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="27">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="27" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">3.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">(A) A director who is a current partner or employee of a firm that is the Company&#146;s internal or external auditor;
(B)&nbsp;a director who has an immediate family member who is a current partner of such a firm; (C)&nbsp;a director who has an immediate family member who is a current employee of such a firm and personally works on the Company&#146;s audit; or
(D)&nbsp;a director who was or whose immediate family member was within the last three years a partner or employee of such a firm and personally worked on the Company&#146;s audit within that time, in any such instance ((A)-(D)) is not independent.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="27">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="27" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">4.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">A director who is or has been within the last three years, or whose immediate family member is, or has been within the
last three years, employed as an executive officer of another company where any of the Company&#146;s present executive officers at the same time serves or served on that company&#146;s compensation committee, is not independent.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="27">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="27" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">5.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">A director who is a current employee, or whose immediate family member is a current executive officer, of a company that
has made payments to, or received payments from, the Company for property or services in an amount which, in any of the last three fiscal years, exceeds the greater of $1&nbsp;million, or 2% of such other company&#146;s consolidated gross revenues,
is not independent. </P></TD></TR></TABLE></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>

<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #0033a0; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="4"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right" STYLE="padding-bottom:2pt ;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #0033a0; padding-left:8pt"><I><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom">


<IMG SRC="g867884g23_51.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</SUB>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2020 Proxy Statement&nbsp;&nbsp;</I></TD>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has affirmatively determined that Mmes.&nbsp;Andrade and Docherty and Messrs. Boynton, Clough, Hedgebeth, Henry,
Herling, and Stoeckert are independent under the listing standards of the New York Stock Exchange and the categorical standards described above. The Board has determined that the members of the Audit and Ethics Committee (the &#147;Audit
Committee&#148;) and the Compensation Committee meet the heightened independence requirements for service on the Audit Committee and Compensation Committee set forth in
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
the respective committees&#146; charters. In addition, the Board has determined that the members of the Compensation Committee are <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;non-employee</FONT>
directors&#148; (within the meaning of Rule <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">16b-3</FONT> of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#147;Exchange Act&#148;)) and, to the extent necessary to qualify compensation incentives for 162(m)
Transition Relief, &#147;outside directors&#148; (within the meaning of Section&nbsp;162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended (the &#147;Code&#148;)).
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_6"></A>Committees of the Board
</B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has four standing committees: the Audit Committee, Compensation Committee, Corporate Governance and Nominating
Committee (the &#147;Corporate Governance Committee&#148;) and Finance and Strategy Committee (the &#147;Finance Committee&#148;). Each committee has a separate chairperson and
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
each of the committees is composed solely of independent directors. The charters for each of the committees describe the specific authority and responsibilities of each committee and are
available on our website at www.brinks.com. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Committee Membership as of
December&nbsp;31, 2019 </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Audit Committee </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee oversees management&#146;s conduct of the Company&#146;s financial reporting process and the integrity of its financial statements, including the
Company&#146;s accounting, internal controls and internal audit function and its cybersecurity posture and efforts. The Audit Committee also evaluates the qualifications and performance of the Company&#146;s independent auditors, assesses the
independence of the Company&#146;s independent auditors and oversees the annual independent audit of the Company&#146;s financial statements and the Company&#146;s legal and regulatory compliance, as well as ethics programs. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has identified each of Ms.&nbsp;Andrade and Messrs. Clough and Stoeckert as an &#147;audit committee financial expert&#148; as that term is defined in the
rules promulgated by the Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#147;SEC&#148;). The Board has also determined that each of the members of the Audit Committee is financially literate under New York Stock Exchange standards. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Compensation Committee </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation
Committee is responsible for overseeing the policies and programs relating to the compensation of the Chief Executive Officer, and other senior executives, including policies governing salaries, incentive compensation and terms and conditions of
employment. For a further discussion of
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
the Compensation Committee, see &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Corporate Governance Committee </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Corporate Governance Committee is responsible for identifying individuals qualified to become Board members consistent with criteria approved by the Board and recommending to the Board director nominees. The Corporate Governance Committee also
oversees the corporate governance of the Company, including recommending to the Board the Governance Policies, and the annual evaluation of the Board&#146;s performance. In addition, the Corporate Governance Committee recommends to the Board any
changes in <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Finance Committee </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Finance Committee monitors the Company&#146;s strategic direction, including its acquisition strategy, recommends to the Board dividend and other actions and
policies regarding the financial affairs of the Company, and is responsible for oversight of the Company&#146;s 401(k) Plan and the Frozen Pension Plan, and any similar plans that may be maintained from time to time by the Company. The Finance
Committee has authority to adopt amendments to the Company&#146;s 401(k) Plan and the Frozen Pension and Pension Equalization Plans.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_7"></A>Director Nominating
Process </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Corporate Governance Committee regularly engages in succession planning for the Board. In accordance with the
Governance Policies and the Corporate Governance Committee charter, the Corporate Governance Committee periodically assesses whether any vacancies on the Board are expected due to retirement or other factors and considers possible director
candidates. The Corporate Governance Committee has used professional search firms to identify candidates based upon the director membership criteria described in the Governance Policies. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Corporate Governance Committee&#146;s charter provides that the Corporate Governance Committee will consider director candidate recommendations by shareholders.
Shareholders should submit any such recommendations to the Corporate Governance Committee through the method described below under &#147;Communications with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Management</FONT>
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
Members of the Board of Directors.&#148; In accordance with the Company&#146;s bylaws, any shareholder of record entitled to vote for the election of directors at a meeting of shareholders may
nominate persons for election to the Board, if the shareholder complies with the notice procedures set forth in the bylaws and summarized in the section of this proxy statement entitled &#147;Other Information&#151;Shareholder Proposals and Director
Nominations&#148; on page 79. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Corporate Governance Committee evaluates all director candidates in accordance with the director membership criteria described in
the Governance Policies. The Corporate Governance Committee evaluates any candidate&#146;s qualifications to serve as a member of the Board based on the skills and characteristics of individual Board members as well as the composition of the Board
as a whole, the balance of management and independent directors, and the need for particular expertise. In addition,
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>

<TD WIDTH="96%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #0033a0; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="4"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="right" STYLE="padding-bottom:2pt ;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #0033a0; padding-left:8pt"><I><SUB STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:bottom">


<IMG SRC="g867884g23_51.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</SUB>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2020 Proxy Statement&nbsp;&nbsp;</I></TD>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">while there is not specific weight given to any one factor, the Corporate Governance Committee will evaluate a
candidate&#146;s business experience, diversity, international background or experience, the number of other directorships held, leadership capabilities, and any other skills or experience that would contribute to the overall effectiveness of the
Board of Directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">When considering a director standing for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election</FONT> as a nominee, in addition to the attributes
described above, the Corporate Governance Committee considers that individual&#146;s past contribution and future commitment to the Company. The Corporate Governance Committee evaluates the totality of the merits of each prospective nominee that it
considers and does not restrict itself by establishing minimum qualifications or attributes.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">After evaluating any potential director nominees, the Corporate Governance Committee makes a recommendation to the full
Board, and the Board determines the nominees. The evaluation process of prospective director nominees is the same for all nominees, regardless of the source from which the nominee was first identified. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company did not receive any notice of a director candidate recommended by a shareholder or group of shareholders owning more than 5% of the Company&#146;s voting
common stock for at least one year as of the date of recommendation on or prior to November&nbsp;16, 2019, the date that is 120 days before the anniversary date of the release of the prior year&#146;s proxy statement to shareholders.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_8"></A>Board Evaluations
</B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board annually assesses the effectiveness of the full Board and the performance of its committees. The Corporate
Governance Committee is charged
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
with overseeing this process, which includes periodic evaluations by a third party and individual director assessments.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_9"></A>Board Role in Risk
Oversight </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board is responsible for the Company&#146;s overall risk oversight and receives regular reports from management on the
Company&#146;s risk management program (described below) and from the Board&#146;s Audit, Compensation, Corporate Governance, and Finance Committees, each of which is responsible for risk oversight within its area of responsibility. Management is
responsible for the Company&#146;s risk management. Through the Company&#146;s enterprise risk management (&#147;ERM&#148;) program, management identifies and addresses significant risks facing the Company. Under the ERM program, a team of senior
executives identifies and prioritizes risks, and assigns an executive to address each major identified risk area, including by monitoring relevant mitigation plans and processes. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee is responsible for discussing with management the Company&#146;s major financial risk exposures and the steps management has taken to monitor and
control such exposures, including the Company&#146;s risk assessment and risk management policies. As part of its responsibilities, the Audit Committee oversees the Company&#146;s financial policies, including financial risk management. Management
holds regular meetings that identify, discuss and assess financial risk from current
macro-</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
economic, industry and company-specific perspectives. As part of its regular reporting process, management reports and reviews with the Audit Committee the Company&#146;s material financial
risks, proposed risk factors and other public disclosures, mitigation strategies, and the Company&#146;s internal controls over financial reporting. The Audit Committee also engages in periodic discussions with the Chief Financial Officer, the
Controller, the Vice President, Internal Audit and other members of management regarding risks. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each of the other committees of the Board considers risks within its
respective areas of responsibility and regularly reports to the Board on issues related to the Company&#146;s risk profile. The Compensation Committee considers any risks related to the Company&#146;s executive compensation programs and has
oversight responsibility for the Company&#146;s review of all compensation policies and procedures to determine whether they present significant risks. The Corporate Governance Committee considers risks relating to governance and succession
planning. The Finance Committee reviews risks related to strategic transactions and oversees risks related to the Company&#146;s liquidity, credit ratings, and pension and savings plans.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:2pt ;"><B>14&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></TD>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_10"></A>Compensation Risk Assessment </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As part of its oversight of the Company&#146;s executive compensation program, the Compensation Committee reviews and
considers any potential risk implications created by compensation awards. The Compensation Committee believes that the executive compensation program is designed with the appropriate balance of risk and reward in relation to the Company&#146;s
overall business strategy and that the balance of compensation elements does not encourage excessive risk taking. The Compensation Committee will continue to consider compensation risk implications, as appropriate, in designing any new executive
compensation components. In connection with its ongoing risk assessment, the Compensation Committee notes the following attributes of the executive compensation program: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the balance between fixed and variable compensation, short- and long-term compensation, and cash and equity payouts; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the alignment of LTI with selected performance measures that reflect the Company&#146;s business plan, and its financial and operational goals; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the Compensation Committee&#146;s authority to apply negative discretion to annual incentive plan payouts if the Compensation Committee believes that such payouts do not appropriately reflect performance of a particular
executive, the Company or a business unit; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the placement of a significant portion of executive pay &#147;at risk&#148; and dependent upon the achievement of specific corporate performance goals with verifiable results, with
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-established</FONT> threshold, target and maximum payment levels;
</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the use of relative shareholder return as a performance metric for LTI awards; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the Company&#146;s compensation recoupment policy, which applies to performance-based cash and performance-based incentive compensation paid to executive officers and other recipients; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the balance between risks and benefits of compensation as related to attracting and retaining executives and other senior leaders; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the Company&#146;s executive stock ownership guidelines, which align the interests of the executive officers with those of the Company&#146;s shareholders; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">regular review of the executive compensation program by an independent compensation consultant. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation
Committee also has oversight over the Company&#146;s responsibility to review all Company compensation policies and procedures, including the incentives that they create, to assess risk. At the Compensation Committee&#146;s direction, the
Company&#146;s Human Resources Department in partnership with the Internal Audit Department, conducted a risk assessment of the Company&#146;s compensation programs during 2019. Based on its assessment, management concluded that the compensation
policies and practices of the Company and its subsidiaries for employees do not create risks that are reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on the Company, and management presented the results of its assessment to the Compensation
Committee. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_11"></A>Policy and Process for Approval of Related Person Transactions
</B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company has adopted a policy in the Audit Committee&#146;s charter regarding the review and approval of related person
transactions. In the event that the Company proposes to enter into such a transaction, it must be referred to the Audit Committee. The Audit Committee is required to review and approve each related person transaction and any disclosures required by
Item 404 of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K.</FONT> The Audit Committee reviews any related person transactions on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">case-by-case</FONT></FONT> basis. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For purposes of this policy, a &#147;related person transaction&#148; has the same meaning as in Item 404 of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K:</FONT> a
transaction, arrangement or relationship (or any series of related transactions, arrangements or relationships) in which the Company
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
is, was or will be a participant and the amount involved exceeds $120,000 and in which any &#147;related person&#148; has, had or will have a direct or indirect material interest. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For purposes of this policy, a &#147;related person&#148; has the same meaning as in Item 404 of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K:</FONT> any person who
was a director, a nominee for director or an executive officer of the Company during the preceding fiscal year (or an immediate family member of such a director, nominee for director or executive officer) or a beneficial owner of more than 5% of the
outstanding Brink&#146;s Common Stock (or an immediate family member of such owner). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">During 2019, there were no related person transactions under the relevant
standards. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_12"></A>Communications with <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Management</FONT> Members of the Board of Directors </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company&#146;s Governance Policies set forth a process by which shareholders and other interested third parties can
send communications to the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-management</FONT> members of the Board. When interested third parties have concerns, they may make them known to the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-management</FONT> directors
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
by communicating via written correspondence sent by U.S. mail to &#147;Chairman&#148; at the Company&#146;s Richmond, Virginia address. All such correspondence is provided to the Chairman of the
Board at, or prior to, the next executive session held at a regular Board meeting. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_13"></A>Succession Planning
</B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board regularly engages in succession planning for the Chief Executive Officer role. Members of the Board (with
oversight from the Corporate Governance Committee) annually review and discuss an evaluation of potential Chief Executive Officer successors. The Board ensures that meeting
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
agendas for the Board and its committees provide directors with exposure to and opportunities to assess potential successors. The Board annually reviews the emergency succession plan for the
Chief Executive Officer. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_14"></A>Political
Contributions </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In general, it is not the Company&#146;s practice to make financial or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-kind</FONT>
political contributions with corporate assets, even when permitted by applicable law. The Company complies with all applicable state and federal laws related to the disclosure of lobbying activities.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company administers, under federal and state election laws, The Brink&#146;s Company Political Action Committee, which
is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-partisan</FONT> political action committee comprised of the Company&#146;s managerial and professional U.S. employees who voluntarily pool their financial resources to support the Company&#146;s efforts to
promote the business interests of the Company through the legislative process. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_15"></A>Resignation and Retirement </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under the Company&#146;s Governance Policies, a director who retires or whose job responsibilities change materially from
those in effect at the time the director was last elected to the Board should submit his or her resignation to the Board. The Corporate Governance Committee will then review and consider the director&#146;s resignation and make a recommendation to
the Board whether to accept or decline the resignation. In addition, the Board maintains a policy that a director may not stand for election to the Board for any term during which his or her 74th birthday would fall more than six months prior to the
expiration of that term. </P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company&#146;s Governance Policies also provide that any nominee for director in an uncontested election who receives
a greater number of shareholder votes &#147;against&#148; his or her election than votes &#147;for&#148; his or her election must promptly tender his or her resignation to the Board. The Corporate Governance Committee will then evaluate the best
interests of the Company and will recommend to the Board whether to accept or reject the tendered resignation. Following the Board&#146;s determination, the Company will disclose the Board&#146;s decision of whether or not to accept the resignation
and an explanation of how the decision was reached. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_16"></A>PROPOSAL NO. 1&#151;ELECTION OF DIRECTORS
</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In accordance with the Company&#146;s Amended and Restated Articles of Incorporation and bylaws, directors are nominated
for election (or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">re-election)</FONT> to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-year</FONT> terms. Each of the Company&#146;s directors is serving a term that expires in May 2020. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Corporate Governance Committee has recommended, and the Board has approved Mmes.&nbsp;Andrade and Docherty and Messrs. Boynton, Clough, Hedgebeth, Henry, Herling,
Pertz and Stoeckert each as nominees for election to a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-year</FONT> term expiring in 2021. Proxies cannot be voted for a greater number of persons than the number of nominees named in this proxy statement. Unless
otherwise specified, all proxies will be voted in favor of Mmes.&nbsp;Andrade and Docherty and Messrs. Boynton, Clough, Hedgebeth, Henry, Herling, Pertz and Stoeckert for election as directors of the
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
Company. The Board has no reason to believe that any of the nominees is not available or will not serve if elected. If any of them should become unavailable to serve as a director, full
discretion is reserved to the persons named as proxies to vote for such other persons as may be properly nominated. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Set forth below for each director nominee is
information concerning the nominee&#146;s age, principal occupation, employment (including other positions with the Company), directorships during the past five years, and the year in which he or she first became a director of the Company. Also set
forth below is a brief discussion of the specific experience, qualifications, attributes or skills that led to the conclusion that each nominee should serve as a director, in light of the Company&#146;s business and structure.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Criteria for Board Membership </B></P>

criteria for director membership, which include: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

described above, the Corporate Governance Committee considers that individual&#146;s past contribution and future commitment to the Company. The Corporate Governance Committee evaluates the totality of the merits of each prospective nominee that it
considers and does not restrict itself by establishing minimum qualifications or attributes. </P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>NOMINEES FOR ELECTION AS DIRECTORS FOR A
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">ONE-YEAR</FONT> TERM EXPIRING IN 2021 </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; border-bottom:1.00pt solid #999999; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>KATHIE J. ANDRADE
Age: 59</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Director since: 2019</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Audit Committee</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Corporate Governance Committee</B></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms.&nbsp;Andrade is the former Chief Executive Officer of TIAA Retail Financial Services and Chairman of TIAA Federal Savings Bank, a
leading provider of financial services in the academic, research, medical, cultural and governmental fields, having served in this role from 2016 to 2018. Ms.&nbsp;Andrade joined TIAA in 2008 serving as Chief Operating Officer of Individual Advisory

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; border-bottom:1.00pt solid #999999; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>GEORGE I.
STOECKERT Age: 71</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Director since: 2016</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Audit Committee</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Corporate Governance Committee (Chair)</B></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Stoeckert has been a private investor and advisor since 2011. He served as Interim President and Chief Executive Officer of The
Brink&#146;s Company from May 2016 to June 2016, and previously served as President of North America and Internet Solutions at Dun&nbsp;&amp; Bradstreet from 2009 to 2011. Prior to that, he held various senior leadership positions at Automatic Data
Processing, Inc. (&#147;ADP&#148;), including President of Employer Services International and President of the Major Accounts Services Division. Before joining ADP, Mr.&nbsp;Stoeckert served as President of the Insurance Management Services
Division and Senior Vice President of Strategy and Corporate Development at Ryder System, Inc. Mr.&nbsp;Stoeckert currently serves on the Board of Directors of Theragenics, Inc. (a medical device company). He also serves as a Senior Advisor to the
private equity firm, Bridge Growth Partners, LLC. During the past five years, Mr.&nbsp;Stoeckert has also served as a director of Onvia, Inc. (a business intelligence company), and Capital Re Corporation (a financial guarantee company).
Mr.&nbsp;Stoeckert has a broad domestic and international business background, including strategic planning, finance, technology and operational expertise, and brings to the Board significant related-industry experience from his leadership roles at
ADP and Ryder System, Inc. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:3.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><center> <P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #0033a0;width:63%">&nbsp;</P></center>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RECOMMENDS THAT </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>THE SHAREHOLDERS VOTE FOR THE NINE </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>NOMINEES NAMED IN THIS PROXY STATEMENT </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>FOR ELECTION AS DIRECTORS. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><center>
<P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #0033a0;width:63%">&nbsp;</P></center>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_17"></A>PROPOSAL NO. 2&#151;ADVISORY VOTE TO APPROVE
NAMED EXECUTIVE OFFICER COMPENSATION </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company is seeking shareholder approval of an advisory resolution to approve the compensation of the Company&#146;s
named executive officers as disclosed in this proxy statement. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company maintains a pay for performance compensation philosophy and an executive compensation
program that is designed to: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">incentivize and reward executives who contribute to the achievement of the Company&#146;s business objectives and the creation of long-term shareholder value, without encouraging unnecessary and excessive risks;
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">attract, retain and motivate talented executives to perform at the highest level and contribute significantly to the Company&#146;s success; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">align the interests of the named executive officers with those of shareholders through equity-based LTI awards and robust stock ownership guidelines; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">provide an appropriate and balanced mix of short-term and long-term compensation elements. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In deciding how to vote on
this proposal, the Board asks that you consider the following key points with respect to our executive compensation program: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>We pay for performance</I>. The 2019 compensation awarded to the named executive officers reflects the compensation principles listed above as well as the Company&#146;s results for the year. Annual incentive awards
were paid according to the Company&#146;s achievement of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> operating profit, revenue and free cash flow results as well as individual performance. LTI awards consisted of Internal Metric PSU, Relative
TSR PSU, Stock Option and RSU awards to ensure continued alignment between executive officer compensation and long-term shareholder value. Mr.&nbsp;Pertz&#146;s entire 2019 LTI award was provided in performance-based equity &#150; 50% in Internal
Metric PSUs, 25% Relative TSR PSUs and 25% Stock Options. He received no RSUs in 2019.
</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>The Compensation Committee regularly reviews the Company&#146;s executive compensation program</I>. The Compensation Committee reviews the Company&#146;s executive compensation program to ensure that it is aligned
with the competitive market and reflects the compensation principles listed above. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>The executive compensation program is designed to align the interests of executives and shareholders.</I> The LTI program is designed to ensure strong alignment with shareholder value through payment in shares of
Brink&#146;s Common Stock. The Compensation Committee uses a focused peer group that includes companies in similar industries, with similar characteristics to Brink&#146;s as its reference point, as well as relevant survey data, as needed, for
assessing executive officer compensation against the market. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>There are no tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups</FONT> upon a change in control for executive officers and no excessive perquisites</I>. None of the Company&#146;s executive officers is subject to any
agreement or policy that provides excise tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups</FONT> upon a change in control. We provide limited perquisites to our executive officers. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>The Compensation Committee uses an independent compensation consultant</I>. The Compensation Committee&#146;s consultant reports directly to the Committee and does not perform any work for management. In performing
its services, the consultant works closely with management at the Committee&#146;s direction. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>We engage with our shareholders</I>. The Company maintains a shareholder outreach program to connect with shareholders throughout the year to gain insight into shareholders&#146; perspectives on key governance and
compensation issues. </TD></TR></TABLE></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>The Company may take advantage of tax deductibility for compensation of executives to the extent 162(m) Transition Relief is available</I>. The Board and shareholders previously approved an LTI program that is
intended to permit the Company, if appropriate and if permitted, to take tax deductions for payments under Section&nbsp;162(m) of the Code where 162(m) Transition Relief remains available. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">You are encouraged to review the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, the compensation tables and the accompanying narrative on pages 27 through 59 of this proxy
statement, which provide a comprehensive review of the Company&#146;s executive compensation program and its elements, objectives and rationale. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In accordance with
Section&nbsp;14A of the Exchange Act rules, shareholders are asked to approve the following <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</FONT> resolution: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:20pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>&#147;RESOLVED, that the Company&#146;s shareholders approve, on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</FONT> advisory basis, the
compensation of the
</B></P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:20pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>
Company&#146;s named executive officers, as disclosed in the Proxy Statement for the 2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders pursuant to the compensation disclosure rules of the Securities and
Exchange Commission, including the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, the 2019 Summary Compensation Table, the other related tables and the accompanying narrative on pages 27 through 59.&#148; </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company holds this <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</FONT> advisory vote annually. The shareholder vote on this proposal will be <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</FONT> on the Company and the Board and will not be construed as overruling a decision by the Company or the Board. However, the Board and the Compensation Committee value the opinions that shareholders express
in their votes and will consider the outcome of the vote when making future executive compensation decisions as they deem appropriate.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><center>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>SHAREHOLDERS VOTE FOR THE APPROVAL OF THE </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">NON-BINDING</FONT> RESOLUTION ON NAMED </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>EXECUTIVE OFFICER COMPENSATION. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><center>

<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_18"></A>COMPENSATION DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_19"></A>Executive Summary </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

executive officers: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

strong earnings growth in 2019. Following are key financial performance metrics that are monitored by management and the Board, reported to shareholders, and used in determining compensation amounts for the named executive officers.

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>2019 Annual and Long-Term Incentive Payouts </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Incentive program payout determinations for 2019 for the named executive officers reflect the Company&#146;s performance against specific,
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-established</FONT> financial goals. The named executive officers received 2019 annual incentive payouts under the Brink&#146;s Incentive Plan (&#147;BIP&#148;) ranging from approximately 77% to 107% of their
respective targets. These payouts reflect adjusted results that were below both the target <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> operating profit of $415&nbsp;million and the target <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> revenue
of $3.8&nbsp;billion approved by the Compensation Committee, as well as performance against a free cash flow performance goal and performance in the countries within each executive&#146;s area of responsibility (where applicable) and individual
performance factors. See the description of 2019 annual incentive payouts beginning on page 35. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Payouts for Relative TSR PSUs for the 2017 &#150; 2019 performance
period reflect TSR above the 75th percentile of the peer companies (as a result of stock price appreciation from $41.39 per share at the beginning of the performance period to $93.55 at the end of the performance period), which resulted in payment
of 150% of the target Relative TSR PSUs awarded in 2017. Payouts for Internal Metric PSUs for the 2017 &#150; 2019 performance period reflect performance above the target and maximum levels of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT>
operating profit established by the Compensation Committee and resulted in payment to each named executive officer of 200% of the target Internal Metric PSUs awarded in 2017. See pages 40 and 41 for a description of LTI payouts. <B></B> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>2019 Compensation for Chief Executive Officer, Douglas A. Pertz </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The primary components of compensation for the Chief Executive Officer consist of base salary, annual incentive and long-term incentive. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For 2019, the Compensation Committee established an annual incentive target of 135% of Mr.&nbsp;Pertz&#146;s base salary. Mr.&nbsp;Pertz received an annual incentive
payout of $1,309,770 in March 2020, which represented approximately 97% of the target in light of Brink&#146;s performance against the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-established</FONT> performance goals and Mr.&nbsp;Pertz&#146;s individual
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
performance. In February 2019, the Compensation Committee approved an LTI award in the amount of $5,800,000 for Mr.&nbsp;Pertz, which was made up of Internal Metric PSUs, Relative TSR PSUs and
Stock Options. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Executive Compensation Program Changes in 2019 </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2019, the Compensation Committee approved several changes to the executive compensation program, which are further described in this CD&amp;A. These changes include:
</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Inclusion of a free cash flow metric in the Company&#146;s annual incentive plan as a modifier to the payout for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> operating profit and revenue performance.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Transition to time-vested stock options from performance-vesting stock options for all named executive officers. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Re-balancing</FONT> of the CEO&#146;s annual LTI award type mix to 50% IM PSUs, 25% Relative TSR PSUs and 25% time-vested stock options, maintaining an LTI program comprised entirely of
performance-based equity. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>&#147;Say on Pay&#148; Results and Shareholder Engagement </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">At the 2019 annual meeting, approximately 99% of votes cast on the &#147;say on pay&#148; proposal approved the compensation awarded to named executive officers. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee and the Board take into account the results of the &#147;say on pay&#148; vote as they consider the design of the executive compensation
program and policies. There were no changes made to the Company&#146;s executive compensation program in direct response to the 2019 &#147;say on pay&#148; voting results. Members of management and the Board continue to engage in outreach to the
Company&#146;s shareholders to discuss governance and compensation policies and practices and emerging issues. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>COMPENSATION DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_20"></A>Executive Compensation Program Components for 2019 </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Primary Components
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Named executive officer compensation awarded in 2019 consisted of the following primary components. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
