<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Key Employees&#146; Deferred Compensation Program </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Deferrals </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company&#146;s deferred compensation program is an
unfunded plan that provides deferred compensation for a select group of the Company&#146;s management, including the named executive officers. Under the deferred compensation program, a named executive officer is permitted to defer receipt of: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">up to 90% of his or her cash incentive payments awarded under the annual incentive plan (the BIP for 2019 awards and the EIP for 2017 and 2018 awards); </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">up to 50% of his or her base salary; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">any or all amounts that are prevented from being deferred, and the related matching contribution, under the Company&#146;s 401(k)&nbsp;Plan as a result of the limitations imposed by the Internal Revenue Code.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company provides matching contributions for deferred cash incentive amounts (100% of the first 10% deferred) and deferred salary (100% of the
first 10% deferred). An executive may elect to defer additional amounts under the supplemental savings plan after he or she meets the maximum permitted under the company&#146;s 401(k) Plan. The company provides matching contributions to supplemental
savings plan contributions. For 2019, matching contributions were equal to 100% of the first 2.0% of salary and annual incentive deferrals, less amounts deferred into the Company&#146;s 401(k) Plan. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Amounts deferred are invested in mutual funds or converted to units that track Brink&#146;s Common Stock, per the executive&#146;s instructions at the time of annual
enrollment. Matching contributions by the Company are made in the form of units of Brink&#146;s Common Stock, which are subject to a five-year vesting period from the original participation in the deferred compensation program. The dollar values are
converted in accordance with the formula in the program.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dividends paid with respect to the common stock units in a participant&#146;s account are converted to units that track
Brink&#146;s Common Stock. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Distributions </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>General.</I></B>
The deferred compensation program provides for distributions of one share of Brink&#146;s Common Stock for each common stock unit in a participant&#146;s account. Cash is paid for deferred compensation invested in mutual funds, and in lieu of the
issuance of fractional shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Termination Upon Death, Retirement, Disability or Change in Control.</I></B> Upon the termination
of participation as a result of death, retirement, total and permanent disability or termination for any reason within three years following a change in control, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">lump-sum</FONT> distributions for all accrued units
are made under the deferred compensation program six months after termination of employment. A participant may elect, however, to receive the shares in up to five equal annual installments beginning after the last day of the sixth month following
the fifth anniversary of the date of termination. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Termination Other Than Upon Death, Retirement, Disability or Change in Control.</I></B> In the event that a
participant&#146;s employment terminates for a reason not described above, the participant receives the contributions made by the participant, related dividends and changes in market value. The participant forfeits all common stock units
attributable to matching contributions and related dividends for the year in which the termination occurs and the common stock units attributable to matching contributions and related dividends that are otherwise unvested. If a participant&#146;s
employment is terminated for &#145;&#145;cause,&#146;&#146; the participant forfeits all common stock units attributable to matching contributions and related dividends credited to the participant&#146;s account under the program whether or not
vested. A participant&#146;s common stock units attributable to Company matching contributions and related dividends vest based on the number of months since the executive&#146;s original participation in the deferred compensation program:
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION TABLES </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As of December&nbsp;31, 2019, Mr.&nbsp;Beech was fully vested. Messrs. Pertz and Domanico were 50% vested.
Ms.&nbsp;O&#146;Brien and Mr.&nbsp;Shemanski were 0% vested. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Lump-sum</FONT> distributions are made at a date selected by the
participant at least two years following the
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
date of election or six months after termination of employment. A participant may elect, however, to receive the shares in up to five equal annual installments beginning on a date selected by the
participant at least two years following the year of election. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_35"></A>Potential Payments
Upon Termination or Change in Control </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">None of the Company&#146;s named executive officers have employment agreements with the Company, however, each named
executive officer may be eligible to receive benefits and payments pursuant to the Company&#146;s Severance Pay Plan and individual change in control agreements in the event of termination or change in control. Benefits under change in control
agreements are triggered upon termination following change in control (&#147;double trigger&#148;). The tables on pages&nbsp;61 and 65 show the estimated amount of incremental additional benefits and payments that would be paid to each of the named
executive officers if their employment terminated on December&nbsp;31, 2019 to the extent those benefits and payments exceed amounts that would be due to the named executive officers regardless of the reason for termination of employment, including,
for each named executive officer, the aggregate balance of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT> deferred compensation which appears in the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-qualified</FONT> Deferred Compensation Table on page 56,
subject to vesting of Company matching contributions as described under &#147;Key Employees&#146; Deferred Compensation Program&#151;Distributions&#148; beginning on page&nbsp;58. Mr. Zukerman ceased serving as an executive officer on June&nbsp;28,
2019; therefore, he is not including in the tables on pages 61 and 65 and the actual arrangements of his separation from service are described on page 65 under the heading &#147;Terms of Separation for Mr. Zukerman.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Because the named executive officers would be eligible to receive different benefits and payments depending on whether a change in control had occurred on
December&nbsp;31, 2019, information about the additional benefits and payments that would be paid to each named executive officer in connection with a termination of employment is presented in two tables: one without a change in control and one with
a change in control. Following are descriptions of the types of benefits and payments that the named executive officers would be eligible to receive under various termination scenarios, key terms under the change in control agreements, and the
categories of benefits and payments as reflected in the tables on pages 61 and 65.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Severance Pay Plan </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Upon a qualifying termination, participants who are named executive officers would be eligible to receive the following benefits: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">a lump sum payment equal to the sum of: (a)&nbsp;the executive&#146;s annual base salary through the date of termination, (b)&nbsp;any bonus or incentive compensation approved but not paid, and (c)&nbsp;any accrued
vacation pay, in each case to the extent not already paid or credited as of the date of termination; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">a lump sum payment equal to the product of (a)&nbsp;one (one and a half (1.5) for the Chief Executive Officer), multiplied by (b)&nbsp;the sum of annual base salary and target annual incentive opportunity;
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">a prorated bonus for the year of termination, so long as the participant was employed by the company for at least six months of the performance year; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">reimbursement payments for continued medical and dental benefit coverage until the earlier of 12 months (18 months for the Chief Executive Officer) following the date of termination and such time as the participant
becomes eligible to receive medical and dental benefits under another employer-provided plan; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">continued vesting of equity awards granted in connection with the Company&#146;s ordinary LTI award grant cycle until the first anniversary of the participant&#146;s date of termination with payout at lower of target or
actual performance; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">reasonable outplacement services during the period over which the health care benefits are provided. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In order to receive severance payments, the participant must execute a separation and release agreement that includes a
release of claims in favor of the Company as well as confidentiality, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-solicitation</FONT> and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-competition</FONT> restrictions that remain in effect for a period of 12 months
after termination of employment (18 months for the Chief Executive Officer). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee may amend or terminate the Severance Pay Plan at any time, but any action
that would reduce the payments or benefits to participants, narrow the conditions for a qualifying termination, or otherwise reduce the protections provided to participants would not be effective until 12 months following approval by the Committee.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Hypothetical Post-Employment Payments and Benefits to Named Executive Officers Without a Change in Control </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The table on page 61 provides information with respect to incremental additional hypothetical benefits and payments to the named executive officers as of
December&nbsp;31, 2019 under the Company&#146;s policies and programs, assuming their employment was terminated without a change in control. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The amounts in the
following tables are in the following categories: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">In the event of incapacity, short-term disability payments are payable by the Company for the first six months during the
disability period. Such payments cover 100% of the executive&#146;s base salary. The amounts represent the net present value of such disability payments, discounted at 1.91%. Amounts under the Company&#146;s long-term disability program are not
included as they are provided on a broad basis to U.S. employees. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

times the executive&#146;s base salary under the Executive Salary Continuation Plan. These amounts represent the net present value discounted at 2.17%. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(3)</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Unvested options are valued based on the difference between the closing price of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at
December&nbsp;31, 2019 and the option&#146;s exercise price. If the option&#146;s exercise price is less than the December&nbsp;31, 2019 price, no value is attributed to the unvested option. Unvested RSUs are valued based on the number of unvested
units multiplied by the closing price of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at December&nbsp;31, 2019. Unvested Relative TSR PSUs and Internal Metric PSUs, are valued in accordance with plan terms, based on the number of unvested units multiplied by the
closing price of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at December&nbsp;31, 2019. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Hypothetical Termination Benefits Following Termination Upon a Change in Control
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Change in Control Agreements </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The change in control agreements provide certain compensation and continued benefits in the event that a &#147;change in control&#148; occurs. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, these agreements provide additional benefits and payments in the event that a change in control occurs and either the executive is terminated by the Company
other than for &#145;&#145;cause&#146;&#146; or incapacity or he resigns for &#145;&#145;good reason&#146;&#146; within two years following a change in control. Each named executive officer is a party to a change in control agreement with the
Company with principal terms as described below. The executive&#146;s entitlement to benefits under the agreement requires compliance with certain <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-competition</FONT> provisions. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Change in Control Agreements&#151;Definitions of Key Terms </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The change
in control agreements generally define &#147;cause,&#148; &#147;change in control&#148; and &#147;good reason&#148; as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;cause&#148; means embezzlement, theft or misappropriation of any property of the Company, the willful breach of any fiduciary duty to the Company, the willful failure or refusal to comply with laws or regulations
applicable to the Company and its business or the policies of the Company governing the conduct of its employees, gross incompetence in the performance of job duties, commission of a felony or of any crime involving moral turpitude, fraud or
misrepresentation, the failure to perform duties consistent with a commercially reasonable standard of care or any gross negligence or willful misconduct resulting in a loss to the Company. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">a &#147;change in control&#148; generally will be deemed to have occurred: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="61">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">upon any (1)&nbsp;combination of the Company in which the Company is not the surviving entity or upon certain conversion of all of the shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock (2)&nbsp;sale, lease, exchange or other transfer
(in one transaction or a series of transactions) of all or substantially all the assets of the Company;
</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="61">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">when any third-party becomes the beneficial owner of more than 20% of the total voting power of the Company; or </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="61">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">if at any time during a period of two consecutive years, individuals who at the beginning of such period constituted the Board cease for any reason to constitute at least a majority thereof, unless the election by the
Company&#146;s shareholders of certain new directors during such <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-year</FONT> period was approved by a vote of at least <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-thirds</FONT> of the directors then still in office who
were directors at the beginning of such <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-year</FONT> period. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;good reason&#148; generally means: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="61">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">material diminution in the named executive officer&#146;s position, authority, duties or responsibilities; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="61">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">material breach of or failure by the Company to comply with its obligations under the change in control agreement; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="61">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">a change to the named executive officer&#146;s work location that increases the distance of the executive&#146;s commute by a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-determined</FONT> amount; or </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="61">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the failure by the Company to require any successor entity to assume the applicable agreement and agree to perform the Company&#146;s obligations under the applicable agreement; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>provided, however</I>, that good reason will cease to exist if the named executive officer has not terminated employment within two years following the initial occurrence of the event constituting good reason.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For Mr.&nbsp;Pertz, &#147;good reason&#148; means any of the following events that is not cured by the Company within 30 days after written notice
thereof from Mr.&nbsp;Pertz to the Company, which written notice must be made within 90 days of the occurrence of the event: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">without Mr.&nbsp;Pertz&#146;s written consent, the assignment of duties materially inconsistent with his position, duties
or responsibilities (including reduction of duties related to the Company as a public company, such that those duties no longer constitute a
</P></TD></TR></TABLE></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">removal from the Board (other than for Cause) or the failure to be renominated for election to be a member of the Board at the expiration of a term (excluding failure to be reelected to the Board by the shareholders);
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">without Mr.&nbsp;Pertz&#146;s written consent, the Company&#146;s requiring him to change his work location by a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-determined</FONT> amount; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">a material reduction in annual base salary or target annual incentive opportunity (other than in connection with a reduction that applies to employees of the Company and its Subsidiaries generally); or
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">material breach of, or failure by the Company to comply with, the provisions of the Change in Control Agreement. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Change in Control Agreements&#150;Benefits Following a Change in Control if Executive is not Terminated </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Salary and Annual Incentive.</I></B> During the first two years of employment following a change in control, each executive who is a party to a change in control
agreement will receive annual compensation at least equal to the sum of (1)&nbsp;a salary not less than the executive&#146;s annualized salary in effect immediately before the change in control occurred, plus (2)&nbsp;a bonus not less than the
amount of the executive&#146;s average annual incentive award for the last three years preceding the date the change in control occurred. In the event the executive has not been employed with the Company for the last three years, the
executive&#146;s target annual incentive will be used for any partial or complete year as necessary to determine the three year average. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Incentive, Savings
and Retirement Plans.</I></B> During the executive&#146;s continued employment, the executive is entitled to continue to participate in all available incentive and savings plans and programs offered by the Company. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Welfare Benefit Plans.</I></B> During the executive&#146;s continued employment, the executive and/or the executive&#146;s family or beneficiary, as the case may
be, is eligible to participate in and will receive all benefits under generally available welfare benefit plans and programs offered by the Company.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Change in Control Agreements&#150;Termination Benefits Following a Change in Control </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Termination for Good Reason or for Reasons Other Than for Cause, Death or Incapacity. </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under this scenario: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Company will make a lump sum cash payment to the executive consisting of the aggregate of the following amounts: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="61">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the sum of (1)&nbsp;the executive&#146;s currently effective annual base salary through the date of termination to the extent not already paid, (2)&nbsp;any bonus or incentive compensation in respect of a completed
performance period, but not paid as of the date of termination, (3)&nbsp;a portion of the executive&#146;s average annual incentive awarded during the past three years <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pro-rated</FONT> based on the number of days
worked in the year of termination, and (4)&nbsp;any accrued vacation pay, in each case to the extent not already paid or credited (the sum of the amounts described in clauses (1)&nbsp;through (4) is referred to as the &#147;Accrued Obligation
Payment&#148;); and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="61">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">an amount equal to two times the sum of the executive&#146;s annual base salary and average annual incentive awarded during the past three years. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Company will provide the executive with outplacement services. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">To the extent not already paid or provided, the Company will pay or provide any other amounts or benefits required to be paid or provided or that the executive is eligible to receive under any plan, program, policy or
practice or contract or agreement of the Company (such other amounts and benefits are referred to as the &#145;&#145;Other Benefits&#146;&#146;). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">In the event the executive elects continued medical benefit coverage, the Company will reimburse him or her for a period of up to 18 months for premiums associated with such coverage in an amount equal to the premiums
that the Company would have paid for such coverage had employment continued. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Termination for Death or Incapacity.</I></B> If an executive&#146;s employment is terminated by reason of the
executive&#146;s death or incapacity following the date of the change in control, the change in control agreement will terminate without further obligations to the executive&#146;s legal representatives, other than for (1)&nbsp;the payment of the
Accrued Obligation Payment and (2)&nbsp;the provision by the Company of death benefits or disability benefits, respectively, in accordance with the Company&#146;s welfare benefit plans and programs applicable to full-time officers or employees of
the Company as in effect on the date of the change in control or, if more favorable to the executive, at the executive&#146;s deemed date of termination. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Termination for Cause.</I></B> If the Company or its successor terminates an executive&#146;s employment for cause following the date of the change in control, the
change in control agreement will terminate without further obligations to the executive other than payment of (1)&nbsp;a lump sum payment of the executive&#146;s currently effective annual base salary through the date of termination and
(2)&nbsp;Other Benefits, in each case to the extent not already paid or credited. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Termination Other Than for Good Reason.</I></B> If an executive voluntarily
terminates employment following the date of the change in control, excluding a termination for good reason, the change in control agreement will terminate without further obligations to the executive, other than for the lump sum payment of the
Accrued Obligation Payment (with the exception of any <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pro-rated</FONT> annual incentive) and Other Benefits. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Excise Tax
Cutback.</I></B> If the amounts payable to an executive under the change in control agreement trigger payment of an excise tax, an accounting firm designated by the Company prior to the change in control will determine the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">after-tax</FONT> benefit to the executive: (1)&nbsp;with the full payment of amounts due and payment by the executive of any resulting excise tax; and (2)&nbsp;after reducing the payment benefits to the extent necessary to
avoid triggering the excise tax
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
liability. The executive will be paid the amount that produces the greater <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">after-tax</FONT> benefit and any excise tax will be paid by the executive. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Hypothetical Post-Employment Payments and Benefits to Named Executive Officers Upon a Change in Control </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The table on page 65 provides information with respect to the incremental additional benefits and payments to the named executive officers as of December&nbsp;31, 2019
under the scenarios covered by the change in control agreements described above and the Company&#146;s policies and programs assuming their employment is terminated following a change in control. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The amounts in the tables are in the following categories: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B><I>Accrued Obligation Payment</I></B> (as defined on page 63). </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B><I>Base Salary and Annual Incentive.</I></B> Includes a payment equal to two times the executive&#146;s annual base salary and average annual incentive awarded during the past three years. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

medical benefit coverage for up to 18&nbsp;months. </TD></TR></TABLE></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">In the event of incapacity, short-term disability payments are payable by the Company for the first six months during the
disability period. Such payments cover 100% of the executive&#146;s base salary. The amounts represent the net present value of such disability payments, discounted at 1.91%. Amounts under the Company&#146;s long-term disability program are not
included as they are provided on a broad basis to U.S. employees. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

times the executive&#146;s base salary under the Executive Salary Continuation Plan. These amounts represent the net present value discounted at 2.17%. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(3)</SUP></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Unvested options are valued based on the difference between the closing price of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at
December&nbsp;31, 2019, and the option&#146;s exercise price. If the option&#146;s exercise price is less than the December&nbsp;31, 2019 price, no value is attributed to the unvested option. Unvested RSUs are valued based on the number of unvested
units multiplied by the closing price of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at December&nbsp;31, 2019. Unvested Relative TSR PSUs and Internal Metric PSUs are valued in accordance with plan terms, based on the number of unvested units multiplied by the
closing price of Brink&#146;s Common Stock at December&nbsp;31, 2019. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Terms of Separation for Mr.&nbsp;Zukerman
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As previously noted in this proxy statement, Mr.&nbsp;Zukerman entered into a Consulting Agreement with the Company on May&nbsp;8, 2019 in connection
with a transition in his role from Executive Vice President of the Company to a non-executive employee, reporting to the CEO in a consultant capacity. Recognizing Mr.&nbsp;Zukerman&#146;s nearly <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">25-year</FONT> tenure
with the Company and deep experience with the Brink&#146;s Global Services (&#147;BGS&#148;) business, the agreement was designed to ensure a smooth transition of leadership with respect to his responsibilities in various areas, including customer
relations, management succession planning within his organization, implementation of BGS strategy and integration activities of recent and planned M&amp;A activity, for </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

consulting agreement provided for the following items: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

based on service through June&nbsp;30, 2019; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Continued retirement, medical and other benefits. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Additionally, in connection with this agreement, Mr. Zukerman: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Forfeited his 2019 annual LTI grant in its entirety, which had a grant date fair value of $1,249,885;
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Will not be eligible for any future annual or long-term incentive awards in 2019, 2020 or 2021; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Will not receive any cash severance benefits (if Mr. Zukerman were terminated pursuant the Severance Pay Plan, he would
have received one times the sum of base salary and target bonus, health and welfare benefits for 12&nbsp;months and continuation of vesting of annual equity awards for one year); and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

confidential information, non-competition and non-solicitation of customers and employees during the remainder of his employment period. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Despite
the continued employment arrangement under the Consulting Agreement through 2021 (during which <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-2019</FONT> equity awards will continue to vest in the normal course), the Agreement was a modification of
Mr.&nbsp;Zukerman&#146;s outstanding equity awards pursuant to FASB ASC Topic&nbsp;718, resulting in a new fair value for awards granted prior to 2019. The aggregate value of all modified equity awards as of the date of the Consulting Agreement, as
well as the 2019 equity awards that were subsequently forfeited, is shown in the Summary Compensation Table (approximately $10.5&nbsp;million, of which $9.3&nbsp;million is associated with the modification of the outstanding <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-2019</FONT> equity awards). The $9.3&nbsp;million fair value of the modified awards was driven primarily by the higher price of the Company&#146;s stock price at the date the awards were modified. The actual value of
the pre-2019 (modified) awards that will be realized by Mr. Zukerman will be determined based on stock price at the date of settlement and performance against pre-established financial goals, as applicable. No new equity grants were made in
connection with the Consulting Agreement. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The table below represents the payments made or projected to be made to Mr.&nbsp;Zukerman in accordance with the terms of

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION TABLES </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_36"></A>Chief Executive Officer Pay Ratio for 2019 </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Pursuant to Item 402(u) of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K</FONT> promulgated under the Exchange Act, as
mandated by the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act, we are required to disclose the median annual total compensation of all of the Company&#146;s employees, the total compensation of the Company&#146;s chief executive officer,
and the ratio of these two amounts. The methodology that we used and the material assumptions, adjustments and estimates that we used to identify the median employee and then determine annual total compensation for 2019 were as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In determining the median total compensation of all employees, we prepared a list of all employees as of December&nbsp;31, 2019 and the taxable wages (determined in
accordance with local laws in each jurisdiction in which the Company&#146;s employees are employed) for each employee for 2019. We included all employees, whether employed on a full-time, part-time or seasonal basis. 2019 taxable wages were
annualized for any employees who joined the Company after January&nbsp;1, 2019. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We then identified the median total compensation among the list of taxable wages for
these
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
64,901&nbsp;employees. In determining the median total compensation of all employees, we did not make any cost of living adjustments to the wages paid to any employee outside of the U.S. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As set forth in the table below, our chief executive officer to global median employee pay ratio is 679:1 for 2019. As described in the Compensation
Discussion&nbsp;&amp; Analysis, the Compensation and Benefits Committee reviews and approves target compensation for the Company&#146;s Chief Executive Officer, taking into account relevant market data and the executive&#146;s performance and
expected future contributions to the Company. In 2019, approximately 88% of the CEO&#146;s target compensation was performance-based, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">at-risk</FONT> compensation. Compensation for employees other than the
Company&#146;s senior executives, including the median employee, are determined by local management, taking into account relevant market data for that geography, criticality of the employee&#146;s role, and the employee&#146;s performance and
expected future contributions to the Company. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; text-indent:0.50em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>Annual Compensation</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Facts to Consider Regarding Our Employees </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Company&#146;s employees are located in 45 countries. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Approximately 82% of the Company&#146;s employees are located outside of the U.S. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="34">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="19" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Of this 82%, approximately 82% are located in lower wage geographies, where the average annual salary is less than 50% of the average salary for our U.S. employees. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Given that 82% of the Company&#146;s employees are located outside of the U.S., mostly in lower wage geographies, and that a vast majority of the positions are hourly
direct labor, many of whom are temporary or seasonal employees, whose compensation is not annualized per the SEC rules, the compensation of our median global employee (who is employed
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
outside of the U.S.) is significantly lower than our U.S. employee base, which leads to a higher global chief executive officer pay ratio. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In light of the significant percentage of employees located outside of the U.S., we also conducted a review of the 2019 taxable wages employees in the U.S. We included
all employees, whether employed on a full-time, part-time, or seasonal basis. 2019 taxable wages were annualized for any employees who joined the Company after January&nbsp;1, 2019. We then identified the median total compensation among the list of
taxable wages for these 11,823 employees. The median U.S. employee&#146;s total annual compensation for 2019 was $37,021 and the ratio of the chief executive officer to the median U.S. employee&#146;s total annual compensation was 227:1.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The pay ratios included in this information are reasonable estimates, calculated in a manner consistent with Item 402(u)
of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K.</FONT> Given the different methodologies that various
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
public companies will use to determine an estimate of their ratio, the estimated CEO pay ratio information provided herein should not be used as a basis for comparison between companies.

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Directors are eligible to receive a special meeting fee in the event that the Board or its committee holds more than five
additional meetings (other than those planned for the year) in the amount of $1,750 per in-person meeting and $1,500 per telephonic meeting. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Director Equity </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under the terms of the 2017 Equity Incentive Plan (approved by shareholders in May 2017), directors received equity
awards, including the annual grant of Deferred Stock Units (&#147;DSUs&#148;). Pursuant to the terms of the plan, the Board may grant <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors equity awards, including options, stock appreciation
rights, restricted stock, other stock-based awards or any combination thereof. The exercise price of any stock option, the grant price of any stock appreciation right, and the purchase price of any security that may be purchased under any other
stock-based award may not be less than 100% of the fair market value of the stock or other security on the date of the grant of the option, right or award. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under
the 2017 Equity Incentive Plan, determinations of the fair market value of shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock are based on the closing price on the grant
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
date and determinations of fair market value with respect to other instruments are made in accordance with methods or procedures approved by the Committee. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2019, directors received grants of DSUs that vest and will be settled in Brink&#146;s Common Stock on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-for-one</FONT></FONT> basis on the first anniversary of the grant date. In general, DSUs are forfeited if a director leaves before the vesting date. The Chairman of the Board receives a portion of his annual fee in the
form of Brink&#146;s Common Stock and certain directors elected to receive all or a portion of their 2019 annual retainers and/or fees in the form of Brink&#146;s Common Stock. More information about Common Stock held by directors appears under
&#147;Stock Ownership&#148; beginning on page 72.</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc867884_38"></A>Stock Ownership Guideline </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors are required to meet a stock ownership guideline of five
times the annual retainer. Until a director has met the ownership guideline, he or she must hold at least 50% of any shares acquired through vesting of equity awards. The Corporate Governance Committee annually reviews directors&#146;
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
compliance with the guideline. Shares counted towards the ownership guideline include Brink&#146;s Common Stock, deferred stock units, shares of restricted stock, and unvested and vested
restricted stock units, but not unexercised stock options. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Plan for Deferral of Directors&#146; Fees
</B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under the Plan for Deferral of Directors&#146; Fees (the &#147;Deferral Plan&#148;), a director may elect to defer receipt
of his or her cash retainer, fees, and/or dividend equivalent payments (for equity awards prior to 2017) to future years, into one or more investment options, in amounts between 10% and 100%. Distributions from a director&#146;s account, which may
be made before or after a director ceases to be a member of the Board, generally will be made in a single lump sum distribution; however, a director may elect, in accordance with the Deferral Plan, to receive a
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
distribution in up to ten equal annual installments. Under the Deferral Plan a director may also elect to defer equity awards, including DSUs and retainer fees elected to be paid in shares of
Brink&#146;s common stock. Distributions of deferred equity awards will be made in a single lump sum distribution of Brink&#146;s Common Stock on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-for-one</FONT></FONT> basis.
Directors may elect to have these deferred equity awards distributed on a specified date, or after their separation from service on the Board.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Business Travel Accident Insurance Plan </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company provides directors with insurance benefits payable in the event of their death, dismemberment, loss of sight,
speech, hearing or
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
permanent and total disability if the loss occurs as a result of an accident while the director is traveling on Company business.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Director Compensation Table </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table presents information relating to total
compensation of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2019. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Represents fees earned before deferral of any amounts under the Plan for Deferral of Directors&#146; Fees and fees earned
in cash, but elected to be paid in shares of the Company&#146;s common stock. Ms. Andrade&#146;s fees reflect her appoinment to the Board in August 2019. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Stock to each <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director under the terms of the 2017 Equity Incentive Plan and the grant date fair value of stock awards made to Mr.&nbsp;Herling as a portion of his compensation for service as <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Executive</FONT> Chairman of the Board. For Ms.&nbsp;Andrade, includes a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pro-rated</FONT> DSU award in connection with her appointment to the Board in August 2019.

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">The grant date fair value was computed in accordance with FASB ASC Topic 718 based on the closing quoted sale prices of
Brink&#146;s Common Stock, as reported on the New York Stock Exchange on May&nbsp;2, 2019 (for all directors except Ms. Andrade) and on August&nbsp;8, 2019 (for Ms.&nbsp;Andrade), the respective dates of grant. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Represents total interest on directors&#146; fees deferred under the Plan for Deferral of Directors&#146; Fees. Under the
deferral plan, a director may elect to defer receipt of his or her fees to future years and to receive interest thereon, compounded quarterly, at the prime commercial lending rate of JPMorgan Chase, as of the end of the previous calendar quarter.
Directors may also elect to have deferred fees notionally invested in one or more mutual funds (which mirror funds available under the Key Employees&#146; Deferred Compensation Plan). For a discussion of the material terms of the deferral plan, see
&#147;Plan for Deferral of Directors&#146; Fees&#148; on page 70. There is no pension plan for the Board. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Reflects the value of the perquisites and other personal benefits provided to certain non-employee directors in 2019 in
connection with attendance at a meeting of the Board of Directors. For purposes of computing the dollar amounts of the items listed below, the Company used the actual cost of providing the perquisite or other personal benefit to the non-employee
director. Includes 2019 matching charitable awards made by Brink&#146;s in 2019 as part of the Company&#146;s matching gifts program (which is available to all employees and directors of the Company), in the amounts of $10,000 for Mr.&nbsp;Boynton,
$10,000 for Mr.&nbsp;Herling, and $10,000 for Mr.&nbsp;Stoeckert. Under the Company&#146;s matching gifts program, the Company matches charitable gifts made by full-time employees and directors to eligible educational and cultural institutions,
social service community organizations, hospitals and environmental organizations. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="92%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="87%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="9%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:7pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="padding-bottom:3pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0.57em; font-size:7pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>Name</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" ALIGN="center" STYLE="padding-bottom:3pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #0033a0"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:7pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>Personal
and</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:7pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>Spousal Travel<BR>and<BR>Entertainment</B></FONT></P></TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Directors&#146; Stock Accumulation Plan </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Prior to 2015, the Board granted awards of Directors&#146; Stock Accumulation Plan units (&#147;DSAP Units&#148;) under
the Directors&#146; Stock Accumulation Plan, which expired by its terms on May&nbsp;15, 2015. DSAP Units vested one year from their grant dates and are settled in Brink&#146;s Common Stock on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-for-one</FONT></FONT> basis after a director&#146;s separation from service on the Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table sets forth the
aggregate number of DSAP Units held by each <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director as of December&nbsp;31, 2019 based on previous grants under the Directors&#146; Stock Accumulation Plan. Mmes. Andrade and&nbsp;Docherty and
Messrs. Clough, Henry, and Stoeckert joined the Board after the Directors&#146; Stock Accumulation Plan expired, and therefore do not have any DSAP Units. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_38"></A>STOCK OWNERSHIP </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Directors and Officers </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table shows the beneficial ownership of our common shares as of January&nbsp;10, 2020 by our directors, director nominees, executive officers named in the
Summary Compensation Table, and all of our directors and executive officers as a group. Under applicable SEC rules, the definition of beneficial ownership for purposes of this table includes shares over which a person has sole or shared voting
power, or sole or shared power to invest or dispose of the shares, whether or not a person has any economic interest in the shares, and also includes shares for which the person has the right to acquire beneficial ownership within 60 days of
January&nbsp;10, 2020. Except as otherwise indicated, a person has sole voting and investment power with respect to the shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock beneficially owned by that person. </P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
