<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Also includes, for Mr.&nbsp;Shemanski 20,898 shares pledged to TD Ameritrade in connection with a margin loan and for
Mr.&nbsp;Henry 1,750 shares pledged to Charles Schwab in connection with a margin loan. Such shares were pledged by each of Messrs. Shemanski and Henry prior to January 1, 2020, the effective date of a change in Brink&#146;s policy. As of
January&nbsp;1, 2020, directors and executive officers are no longer permitted to pledge Brink&#146;s securities. See page 45 for additional information. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(b)</SUP></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Each <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director also holds units representing shares of Brink&#146;s
Common Stock that have been credited to his or her account on or prior to January&nbsp;10, 2020: (1) under the 2017 Equity Incentive Plan and the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Employee</FONT> Directors&#146; Equity Plan (Deferred Stock
Units), which will be settled in Brink&#146;s Common Stock on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-for-one</FONT></FONT> basis six months after a director&#146;s separation from service on the Board; (2)&nbsp;under
the 2013 or 2017 Equity Incentive Plan, which will be settled in Brink&#146;s Common Stock on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-for-one</FONT></FONT> basis upon vesting; (3)&nbsp;as a result of compensation
elected to be received in stock and deferred under the Plan for the Deferral of Directors&#146; Fees; and, or (4)&nbsp;as a result of Deferred Stock Units awarded under the 2017 Equity Incentive Plan and the
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Employee</FONT> Directors&#146; Equity Plan that have vested but, pursuant to an election by a director, have been further deferred under the Plan for the Deferral of Directors&#146; Fees. These Deferred Stock
Units are not included in the number of shares of Brink&#146;s Common Stock beneficially owned by such persons. For additional information about the Deferred Stock Units, see &#147;Director Compensation.&#148; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

Section&nbsp;16(a) Reports </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Section&nbsp;16(a) of the
Exchange Act requires the Company&#146;s directors and executive officers, and any persons who own more than 10% of a registered class of the Company&#146;s equity securities, to file with the SEC and the New York Stock Exchange reports of ownership
and changes in ownership of Brink&#146;s Common Stock and other equity securities of the Company. Officers, directors and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">greater-than-10%</FONT> shareholders are required by SEC regulations to furnish the Company
with copies of all Section&nbsp;16(a) forms they file. Based solely on a review of the copies of such reports furnished to the Company or written representations that no other reports were required, the Company believes that, during 2019, its
officers, directors and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">greater-than-10%</FONT> beneficial owners timely filed all required reports, except that, due to administrative errors Forms 4 were not filed within the required period for the following: Dan
Henry, an annual vesting of equity grant; Douglas A. Pertz: (i)&nbsp;reporting the disposition of shares for tax withholding purposes following the settlement of PSU awards and (ii)&nbsp;reporting of vesting of an RSU award; and Amit Zukerman
reporting an open market sale of common stock. In addition a late Form 3 was filed for Raphael J. Shemanski. </P>

<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_42"></A>PROPOSAL NO. 3&#151;APPROVAL OF THE SELECTION OF
INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee has, subject to shareholder approval, selected KPMG LLP (&#147;KPMG&#148;) as the Company&#146;s
independent registered public accounting firm for the fiscal year ending December&nbsp;31, 2020, and the Board recommends approval of such selection by the shareholders. The Audit Committee is directly responsible for the selection, evaluation,
compensation (including negotiation of fees), retention and oversight of the Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm. In order to assure the continued independence of the firm, the Audit Committee periodically considers whether
there should be rotation of the independent registered public accounting firm. In addition, in conjunction with the mandated rotation of the firm&#146;s lead engagement partner, the Audit Committee, led by its Chair, is directly involved in the
selection of the new lead engagement partner. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B><I>Change in Auditor </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">After the conclusion of a competitive auditor selection process, on March&nbsp;2, 2020, the Audit Committee approved the engagement of KPMG to serve as the
Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm and notified Deloitte and Touche LLP (&#147;Deloitte&#148;) of its dismissal. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The dismissal of Deloitte
as the Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm did not result from any dissatisfaction with the quality of professional services rendered by Deloitte. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The audit reports of Deloitte on the Company&#146;s consolidated financial statements as of and for the
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
years ended December&nbsp;31, 2019 and 2018 did not contain an adverse opinion or a disclaimer of opinion, and were not qualified or modified as to uncertainty, audit scope or accounting
principles. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The audit reports of Deloitte on the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting as of December&nbsp;31, 2019 and 2018 did not contain
any adverse opinion or disclaimer of opinion, nor were they qualified or modified as to uncertainty, audit scope, or accounting principles. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">During the
Company&#146;s two most recent fiscal years and in the subsequent interim period prior to March&nbsp;2, 2020, there were no &#147;disagreements&#148; (as that term is described in Item 304(a)(1)(iv) of Regulation
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K</FONT> and the related instructions) or &#147;reportable events&#148; (as that term is described in Item 304(a)(1)(v) of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K)</FONT> with Deloitte on any matter of
accounting principles or practices, financial statement disclosure or auditing scope or procedure, which, if not resolved to the satisfaction of Deloitte, would have caused Deloitte to make reference to the subject matter of such disagreement in
connection with its reports on the financial statements for such periods. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">One or more representatives of KPMG are expected to attend the annual meeting and will
have the opportunity to make a statement if they desire to do so and are expected to be available to respond to appropriate questions. Representatives of Deloitte are not expected to attend the annual meeting.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Principal Accounting Fees and Services
</I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table sets forth the aggregate fees billed by Deloitte, our independent registered public accounting firm for the fiscal years ended
December&nbsp;31, 2019 and December&nbsp;31, 2018. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>PROPOSAL NO. 3&#151;APPROVAL OF THE SELECTION OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC
ACCOUNTING FIRM </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Audit Fees</B> are primarily for professional services provided in connection with the audit of the Company&#146;s
financial statements and review of quarterly consolidated financial statements (including the audit of the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting required by Section&nbsp;404 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002) and audit services
provided in connection with other statutory or regulatory filings. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Audit-Related Fees</B> primarily include fees for assurance services that are reasonably
related to the audit of the Company&#146;s consolidated financial statements and for services in connection with audits of the Company&#146;s pension and other employee benefit plans. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Tax Fees</B> primarily include fees associated with tax compliance and tax advice, as well as domestic and international tax planning. This category also includes tax
planning on mergers and acquisitions and restructurings, as well as other services related to tax disclosure and filing requirements.
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>All Other Fees</B> are for services provided to the Company not otherwise included in the categories above. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Consideration of Auditor Independence </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee has
concluded that the provision of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> services by Deloitte was compatible with maintaining Deloitte&#146;s independence. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Procedures for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Pre-Approval</FONT> of Audit and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Audit</FONT> Services </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee has adopted written procedures for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approving</FONT> audit and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT>
services provided by the independent registered public accounting firm. The <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approved</FONT> services are described in detail under three categories: audit and audit-related, tax services and agreed upon
procedures. Requests for services are reviewed by the members of the Company&#146;s Legal and Finance Departments to ensure that they satisfy the requirements of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approval</FONT> policy. The Audit Committee is
provided a detailed update of these audit and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> engagements at each regular meeting.
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><center>
<P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #0033a0;width:63%">&nbsp;</P></center>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RECOMMENDS THAT THE </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>SHAREHOLDERS VOTE FOR APPROVAL OF THE SELECTION </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>OF KPMG LLP AS THE COMPANY&#146;S INDEPENDENT </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><center>
<P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #0033a0;width:63%">&nbsp;</P></center>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_43"></A>AUDIT AND ETHICS COMMITTEE REPORT </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In accordance with the Audit Committee Charter, the Audit Committee assists the Board in fulfilling its responsibility for oversight of the integrity of the accounting,
auditing and financial reporting practices of the Company. Each member of the Audit Committee is &#147;independent&#148; as required by the applicable listing standards of the NYSE and the rules of the SEC. During the fiscal year ended
December&nbsp;31, 2019, the Audit Committee met eight times, and the Audit Committee reviewed and discussed the financial information contained in the Company&#146;s Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K,</FONT> interim
financial information contained in the Company&#146;s Quarterly Reports on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-Q,</FONT> and discussed press releases announcing earnings with the Company&#146;s Chief Financial Officer and the independent
registered public accounting firm prior to public release. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee members are not professional accountants or auditors, and their functions are not
intended to duplicate or to certify the activities of management or the Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm. The Audit Committee oversees the Company&#146;s financial reporting process on behalf of the Board. The
Company&#146;s management has primary responsibility for the financial statements and reporting process, including the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. The independent registered public accounting firm is responsible for
performing an integrated audit of the Company&#146;s financial statements and internal control over financial reporting in accordance with the auditing standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In connection with the responsibilities set forth in its charter, the Audit Committee has: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">reviewed and discussed the audited financial statements for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31, 2019 with management
and Deloitte, the Company&#146;s independent auditors; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">discussed with Deloitte the matters required to be discussed by the Auditing Standard No.&nbsp;16, Communications with
Audit Committees, which superseded the Statement on Auditing Standards No.&nbsp;61, as amended (AICPA, Professional Standards, Vol. 1. AU section 380), as adopted by the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board in Rule 3200T; and
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">received the written disclosures and the letter from Deloitte required by the applicable requirements of the Public Company
Accounting Oversight Board regarding Deloitte&#146;s communications with the audit committee concerning independence, and has discussed with Deloitte its independence. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Audit Committee also considered, as it determined appropriate, tax matters and other areas of financial reporting and the audit process over which the Audit
Committee has oversight. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Based on the Audit Committee&#146;s review and discussions described above, the Audit Committee recommended to the Board that the audited
financial statements be included in the Company&#146;s Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31, 2019 for filing with the SEC. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:55%; text-indent:-2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Reginald D. Hedgebeth, <I>Chair</I> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:55%; text-indent:-2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Kathie J. Andrade </P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_44"></A>OTHER INFORMATION </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Shareholder Proposals and Director Nominations </B></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Under the regulations of the SEC, any shareholder desiring to submit a proposal pursuant to Rule <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">14a-8</FONT> of the Exchange Act to be acted upon at the 2020 annual meeting of shareholders must cause such proposal to be delivered, in proper form, to the Corporate Secretary at the address provided below under
&#147;Availability of Documents&#148; no later than November&nbsp;27, 2020, in order for the proposal to be considered for inclusion in the Company&#146;s proxy statement for that meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To nominate a director at the annual meeting, a shareholder must satisfy conditions specified in the Company&#146;s bylaws. A shareholder who wishes to suggest potential
nominees to the Board for consideration should write to the Corporate Governance Committee through the method described under &#147;Communications with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Management</FONT> Members of the Board of Directors&#148; on
page 16, stating in detail the qualifications of such nominees for consideration. The Company&#146;s bylaws also prescribe the procedures a shareholder must follow to bring business (other than pursuant to Rule
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">14a-8)</FONT> before annual meetings. For a shareholder to nominate a director or directors at the 2020 annual meeting other than the nomination of a director for inclusion in the Company&#146;s proxy statement, or
bring other business before the 2020
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
annual meeting, notice must be received by the Corporate Secretary at the principal office of the Company not later than the close of business on January&nbsp;8, 2021, nor earlier than the close
of business on November&nbsp;9, 2020. The notice must include a description of the proposed business, the reason for it, the complete text of any resolution and other matters specified in the bylaws. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Any shareholder, or group of up to 20 shareholders, who has owned at least 3% of the outstanding shares of the Company&#146;s Common Stock continuously for at least
three years, is eligible to nominate and include director nominees (up to the greater of 2 or 20% of the number of directors on the Board of Directors) in the Company&#146;s proxy materials for the 2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. Any eligible
shareholder, or group of shareholders, wishing to do so, must give notice in writing of the proposed nomination, along with certain nomination materials, to the Secretary of the Company, delivered by November&nbsp;27, 2020. The notice and
accompanying nomination materials must meet the requirements set forth in the Company&#146;s bylaws. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Any shareholder desiring a copy of the Company&#146;s bylaws
will be furnished one without charge upon written request to the Corporate Secretary. </P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Availability of Documents </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company&#146;s internet address is www.brinks.com. The Company makes available, free of charge, through its website,
its Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K,</FONT> quarterly reports on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-Q,</FONT> current reports on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">8-K</FONT> and amendments to those reports filed
or furnished pursuant to Section&nbsp;13(a) or 15(d) of the Exchange Act. In addition, the Governance Policies, Code of Ethics and the charters of the Audit,
</P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
Compensation, Corporate Governance and Finance Committees also are available on the Company&#146;s website. All of the documents described above are available in print, without charge, to any
shareholder upon request by contacting the Corporate Secretary at 1801 Bayberry Court, P.O. Box 18100, Richmond, Virginia 23226-8100 or by phone at (804) <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">289-9600.</FONT>
</P></div><div style="clear:both; height:0pt; font-size:0pt">&nbsp;</div>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Separate Copies for Beneficial Owners </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Institutions that hold shares in &#147;street name&#148; for two or more beneficial owners with the same address are
permitted to deliver a single proxy statement and annual report to that address. Any such beneficial owner can request a separate copy of this proxy statement or the Company&#146;s Annual Report on
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Form&nbsp;10-K</FONT> for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31, 2019 by contacting the Corporate Secretary at the

address listed above under &#147;Availability of Documents.&#148; Beneficial owners with the same address who receive more than one proxy statement and Annual Report on Form <FONT

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:24pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><A NAME="toc867884_45"></A>APPENDIX A </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-GAAP</FONT> Reconciliation </B></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #0033a0">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This proxy statement refers to
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> revenue, operating profit, and cash flow, which are financial measures that are not required by or presented in accordance with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles (&#147;GAAP&#148;). The
purpose of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> results is to report financial information from the primary operations of our business by excluding the effects of certain income and expenses that do not reflect the ordinary earnings
of our operations. The <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> financial measures are intended to provide investors with a supplemental comparison of our operating results and trends for the periods presented. Our management believes these
measures are also useful to investors as such measures allow investors to evaluate our performance using the same metrics that our management uses to evaluate past performance and prospects for future performance. We do not consider these items to
be reflective of our core operating performance due to the variability of such items from <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">period-to-period</FONT></FONT> in terms of size, nature and significance. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2018 and 2019 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-GAAP</FONT> Results Reconciled to GAAP </B></P>

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">See &#147;Other Items Not Allocated To Segments&#148; below for details. We do not consider these items to be reflective
of our core operating performance due to the variability of such items from period-to-period in terms of size, nature and significance. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(b)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">To adjust for the change in the balance of customer obligations related to cash received and processed in certain of our
secure Cash Management Services operations. The title to this cash transfers to us for a short period of time. The cash is generally credited to customers&#146; accounts the following day and we do not consider it as available for general corporate
purposes in the management of our liquidity and capital resources. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Other Items Not Allocated To Segments (Unaudited) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>The Brink&#146;s Company and subsidiaries </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Brink&#146;s measures its segment
results before income and expenses for corporate activities and for certain other items. See below for a summary of the other items not allocated to segments. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Venezuela operations</B>&nbsp;Prior to the deconsolidation of our Venezuelan subsidiaries effective June&nbsp;30, 2018, we excluded from our segment results all of
our Venezuela operating results, due to the Venezuelan government&#146;s restrictions that have prevented us from repatriating funds.&nbsp;As a result, the Chief Executive Officer, the Company&#146;s Chief Operating Decision maker
(&#147;CODM&#148;), has assessed segment performance and has made resource decisions by segment excluding Venezuela operating results. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Reorganization and
Restructuring </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2016 Restructuring </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In the fourth quarter of 2016,
management implemented restructuring actions across our global business operations and our corporate functions. As a result of these actions, we recognized charges of $18.1&nbsp;million in 2016, an additional $17.3&nbsp;million in 2017 and
$13.0&nbsp;million in 2018. The actions under this program were substantially completed in 2018, with cumulative pretax charges of approximately $48&nbsp;million. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Other Restructurings </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Management periodically implements restructuring actions
in targeted sections of our business. As a result of these actions, we recognized charges of $4.6&nbsp;million in 2017, $7.6&nbsp;million in 2018 and $28.8&nbsp;million in 2019, primarily severance costs. For the current restructuring actions, we
expect to incur additional costs between $1&nbsp;million and $3&nbsp;million in future periods. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Due to the unique circumstances around these charges, these
management-directed items have not been allocated to segment results and are excluded from <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> results. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Acquisitions and dispositions</B><B></B>&nbsp;Certain acquisition and disposition items that are not considered part of the ongoing activities of the business and
are special in nature are consistently excluded from <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> results. These items are described below: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2019 Acquisitions
and Dispositions </I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0"><B>APPENDIX A </B></FONT></P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Compensation expense related to the retention of key Dunbar employees was $4.1&nbsp;million in 2018. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#0033a0">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">We recognized a net gain in 2018 ($2.6&nbsp;million, net of statutory employee benefit) on the sale of real estate in
Mexico. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Argentina highly inflationary impact</B> Beginning in the third quarter of 2018, we designated Argentina&#146;s economy as highly
inflationary for accounting purposes. As a result, Argentine peso-denominated monetary assets and liabilities are now remeasured at each balance sheet date to the currency exchange rate then in effect, with currency remeasurement gains and losses
recognized in earnings. In addition, nonmonetary assets retain a higher historical basis when the currency is devalued. The higher historical basis results in incremental expense being recognized when the nonmonetary assets are consumed. In the
second half of 2018, we recognized $8.0&nbsp;million in pretax charges related to highly inflationary accounting, including currency remeasurement losses of $6.2&nbsp;million. In 2019, we recognized $14.5&nbsp;million in pretax charges related to
highly inflationary accounting, including currency remeasurement losses of $11.3&nbsp;million. These amounts are excluded from <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> results. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Internal loss </B>A former <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-management</FONT> employee in our U.S. global services operations embezzled funds from Brink&#146;s
in prior years. Except for a small deductible amount, the amount of the internal loss related to the embezzlement was covered by our insurance. In an effort to cover up the embezzlement, the former employee intentionally misstated the underlying
accounts receivable subledger data. In 2019, we incurred $4.5&nbsp;million in costs (primarily third party expenses) to reconstruct the accounts receivables subledger. In the third quarter of 2019, we were able to identify $4.0&nbsp;million of
revenues billed and collected in prior periods which had never been recorded in the general ledger. We also identified and recorded $0.3&nbsp;million in bank fees, which had been incurred in prior periods. The rebuild of the subledger was completed
during the third quarter of 2019. Based on the reconstructed subledger, we were able to analyze and quantify the uncollected receivables from prior periods. Although we plan to attempt to collect these receivables, we estimated an increase to bad
debt expense of $13.7&nbsp;million in the third quarter of 2019. The estimate of the allowance for doubtful accounts was adjusted in the fourth quarter of 2019 for an additional $6.4&nbsp;million and will be adjusted in future periods, if needed, as
assumptions related to the collectability of these accounts receivable change.&nbsp;Out of the total $20.1&nbsp;million in bad debt expense recorded in the second half of 2019, $19.2&nbsp;million represented an allowance on $34.0&nbsp;million of
accounts receivable or 56%. Due to the unusual nature of this internal loss and the related errors in the subledger data, along with the fact that management has excluded these amounts when evaluating internal performance, we have excluded these net
charges from segment and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> results. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Reporting compliance</B> Certain compliance costs (primarily third party
expenses) are excluded from <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> results. These costs relate to the implementation and January&nbsp;1, 2019 adoption of the new lease accounting standard ($2.7&nbsp;million in 2018 and $1.8&nbsp;million in
2019) and the mitigation of material weaknesses ($1.8&nbsp;million in 2018 and $0.3&nbsp;million in 2019). </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

 </P> <P STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:0.5pt"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">THE </FONT><br><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:0.5pt" COLOR="#FFFFFF">ANNUAL </FONT><br><FONT

STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:0.5pt" COLOR="#FFFFFF">COMPANY </FONT><br><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:0.5pt" COLOR="#FFFFFF">OF May&nbsp;8, 2020 PROXY VOTING INSTRUCTIONS </FONT><br><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:0.5pt" COLOR="#FFFFFF">- Access &#147;www.voteproxy.com&#148; and follow the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">on-screen</FONT> instructions or scan the QR code with your smartphone. Have your proxy card
available when you access the web page. </FONT><br><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:0.5pt" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Vote online until 11:59 PM EST the day before the meeting. MAIL&#151;Sign, date and mail your proxy card in the envelope
provided as soon as possible. </FONT><br><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:0.5pt" COLOR="#FFFFFF">IN PERSON&#151;You may vote your shares in person by attending the Annual Meeting. </FONT><br><FONT
